Four police officers have been arrested on charges of corruption in Cape Town. Police spokesperson FC van Wyk says a 27-year-old constable stationed at the Belhar Police Station was arrested after he took a bribe from a suspect who was under arrest for the possession of an unlicensed firearm. Van Wyk says two constables and a sergeant, stationed at the Lwandle Police Station, were arrested on Thursday after asking a suspect to pay them in order to evade arrest. Six suspects, including two officers arrested in Pretoria for conspiracy to commit robbery